                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.516/375: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-22T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 22, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Your No. 48, June 19, 10 a.m. Mr. Francis White, Executive Vice President of
                    the Foreign Bondholders Protective Council, called to consult with the
                    Department yesterday. The Department explained its views to Mr. White, who
                    replied that action by the Council would be deferred until meeting of the
                    Executive Committee next week, which may be postponed for a few days owing to
                    the absence of several members of the Committee. The Department believes that
                    the Council will carry out its part in submitting a panel, but this will not
                    definitely be known until after the meeting of the Executive Committee of the
                    Council.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
